SIMPLE: repercussive
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Repercussive
<hw>Re`per*cuss"ive</hw> <pr>(-k?s"?v)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>r⟦eacute⟧percussif</ets>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>Tending or able to repercuss; having the power of
sending back; causing to reverberate.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Ye <qex>repercussive</qex> rocks! repeat the sound.</q>
<rj><qau>W. Pattison.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Repellent.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark> ⟦ldquo⟧Blood is
stanched by astringent and <xex>repercussive</xex> medicines.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>Bacon.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Driven back; rebounding; reverberated.</def>
⟦ldquo⟧Rages loud the <xex>repercussive</xex> roar.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>Thomson.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Repercussive</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Repercussive
<hw>Re`per*cuss"ive</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A repellent.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Bacon.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Repertitious</ent>⟦br⟧
